description:
Late Dynastic vault, Double in construction with 2 separate ban[...] vaults under a single circular top, probably pyramidal (truncated?) originally. Each vault has a separate shaft at its south end. The W. shaft was cleared by Garstany. 
The E vault is broken in above. In it were found:
    Few poor light bl. gl. shabti's.
    Wooden hawk seated, paint worn off.
    Wooden model mummy, roughly covered with bitumen.
    Wooden & stucco f[...] & feather
    Parts of a fringe of hair
    Piece of a large shell.

description:
Pieces of wood coffin with bea[...] hieroglyphs in yellow.
     Two pieces gale[...]
     Blue gl. & yellow gl. cyl.. beads
     Bl. gl. discoid beads.
     Piece gold foil.
Dec. 29  Another wood & stucco hau[...] with feather
     Large wood feather
     Set of smaller bl. gl. shabti's
     Piece of wood with 2 copper(?) rivets.
The tomb is now seen to consist of 3 vaults under one top. The one new [...] is the central. 
    Couns. tooth
    Flat red tile (or part of coffin)

Jan. 1
In the central vault there is one coffin in position at the SW corner. Fine carved coffin of good wood, partly inscribed (on next card). Body mummified with bitumen.

description:
Pieces of wood coffin with "..." hieroglyphs in yellow. 
Two pieces galeha 
Blue glass. large spherical beads.
Blue (...), yellow (...), cylindrical bead, 
Blue (...) discoid bead, 
Piece of golf foil.

Dec 29. Another wood and stucco hawk with feather
Large wood feather
Set of smaller blue "..." Shabtis
Piece of wood with 2 copper (?) rivets. 

The tomb is now seen to consist of 3 vaults under one top. The one now ... is the central. 
Cous Tuoth
Fluint red file (on part of coffin)

Jan. 1. 

In the central vault there is one coffin in position at the S.W. corner. This carved coffin of good wood partly inscribed (and neat cond).
Body mummified via bitumen.
comments:
No name. No number - probably related to Y7? This is because the date matchs (Dec 29th? and onto 1st Jan)
When describing the items found on 29th December the abbreviations used are not totally clear. I'm not sure if he is referring to blue and yellow glass or faience, so have left that blank. I believe it is more likely to be faience?

I love this card! I feel like an archaeologist. It feels like you are discovering the tomb with them in real time!
inputBy: Nadia Randle; Janet Levy; Susan Magyarody
